# Vault Smart Contracts — Standards

## Language constraints (ENFORCED)

Vault runs a **restricted Python sandbox**. These rules are non-negotiable.

### Forbidden — causes runtime rejection

```
# No stdlib imports
import os, sys, json, re, math, datetime, collections, functools,
       itertools, random, hashlib, uuid, logging, requests, http

# No dynamic execution
eval(), exec(), __import__(), compile(), globals(), locals()

# No I/O
open(), print(), input()

# No introspection
getattr(), setattr(), type(), dir(), vars(), isinstance() [generic]

# No mutable globals between hooks
CACHE = {}  # state is lost between hook calls anyway

# No network
requests.get(), socket.connect()

# No exception chaining
raise X from Y
```

### Allowed

```python
# Built-ins
str, int, float, bool, list, dict, tuple, set
len(), range(), enumerate(), zip(), sorted(), sum(), min(), max(), abs(), round()
list/dict comprehensions, f-strings

# Decimal — ALWAYS for money, NEVER float
from decimal import Decimal, ROUND_HALF_UP, ROUND_DOWN

# Vault types only
from contracts_api import (
    BalanceCoordinate, Balance, BalanceDefaultDict,
    Phase, Tside, Posting, CustomInstruction,
    PostingInstructionsDirective, PostingInstructionsDirective,
    Parameter, ParameterLevel, NumberShape, StringShape,
    DenominationShape, UnionShape, UnionItem,
    ScheduledEvent, SmartContractEventType, EndOfMonthSchedule,
    Rejection, RejectionReason,
    ActivationHookArguments, ActivationHookResult,
    PrePostingHookArguments, PrePostingHookResult,
    PostPostingHookArguments, PostPostingHookResult,
    ScheduledEventHookArguments, ScheduledEventHookResult,
)

# Datetime — NEVER import datetime; use hook_arguments.effective_datetime
effective_dt = hook_arguments.effective_datetime  # ZoneInfo-aware
year  = effective_dt.year
month = effective_dt.month
```

