## File structure

```
contracts/
  <product_name>.py          # Smart Contract (snake_case)
tests/
  test_<product_name>.py     # Unit tests
contracts_sdk/               # SDK directory (git-ignored binary)
  contracts_sdk/             # Install from here: py -m pip install .
```

## Commands

```bash
os-stack vault-smart-contracts   # activate stack
os-vault-test                    # run tests with SDK
os-vault-test --coverage         # with coverage ≥ 90%
os-vault-simulate contracts/<product>.py <start> <end> '<params_json>'
os-vault-deploy contracts/<product>.py <product_id> "<display_name>"
os-vault-account <product_version_id> <customer_id>
os-vault-balances <account_id>
```

## Testing standards

- All tests use `ZoneInfo("UTC")` for datetimes
- `BalanceDefaultDict` keyed by `BalanceCoordinate`
- `PrePostingHookArguments` requires `client_transactions={}`
- No `paused_schedule_names` in `ScheduledEventHookArguments`
- Always mock `vault.get_balances_observation().balances` not `vault.get_balance_timeseries()`
- Coverage threshold: **≥ 90%**
- Run: `py -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=contracts --cov-report=term-missing`
